A great market street near the Eiffel Tower and Rodin Museum
Oct 2024 • Solo
Rue Cler is a delightful market street between the Eiffel Tower and the Rodin Museum. Also nearby are the Brandy Museum and the Musee de L’Armee. I visit every time I come to Paris. The street is a great place to purchase the necessities for a picnic on the green below the Eiffel Tower. Unlike supermarkets, rue Cler is a collection of specialty shops — boulangeries, fromageries, wine, butcher and produce shops. There is great dining at the several cafes as well. Several hotels put you right in the middle of this incredible experience.
Written October 9, 2024

Probably past its heyday!
Jul 2024 • Couples
We stayed close by as it is in with walking distance tot the Eiffel Tower. Great street and has everything you need from restaurants, delis, patisseries, cheese shops, gelato, wine shops, etc, but probably past its heyday.

Some empty shops, very quiet during the day, but busier at night. Would have been the hive of activity in its day.

Great food and nice ambiance
Apr 2024 • Couples
We love open air food markets and this pedestrian street is one of the best. We had purchased some meat and cheese at a grocery for snacks but the quality of food on Rue Cler is worth it. Many shops have been there for three generations. We bought bread, cheese macaroons, and sausage. Everything was fabulous. We would go back but we also found great products at the Friday market in Versailles. Highly recommend.

Je déteste Rue Cler
Jul 2023 • Couples
Rue Cler should be Rue Très Cher. The french are nice people and don't deserve their snobbish reputation...unless you're on this street. I tried to take a picture of a business owner chatting with a patron and was chewed out for not asking permission. I tried to buy macaroons and was told by the business owner (different person than picture-gate) that I shouldn't buy them as a gift unless I was giving them to the recipient tomorrow...I got schooled on "freshness.". The street was pretty dead. Maybe because people are sick of all the snobbery. Stay away. It's nothing but people who live in a bubble and are so exclusive that you will get the vibe immediately.
Written February 3, 2024

We decided to visit Rue Cler after reading all the reviews. Unfortunately, we were very underwhelmed and found it to be totally overrated and overpriced. The local markets are equal to or better for shopping for fruit, vegetables, cheeses, breads etc. The restaurants seem to be a better attraction and have a reasonable buzz about them. Ok to visit if in the area but not worth making a special effort to go there.

Hi we stayed at the Hotel Cler....rooms are modern in an ancient building....Beds very comfy, shower great! Staff Wonderful! Insiders tip: If you are going to be using the Metro Monday (start) you can get a ticket for Euro 22 at the train station. It's good for an entire week---including a bus to Charles De Gaulle Airport Just buy a couple of day passes if you are arriving on Sat or Sun. The hotel will scan your passport for you and make a small picture of you for the pass. Hotel Cler did it free of charge. Then you just scan and go....amazing bargain! HAve a wonderful time
